Behavioral management of psychogenic cough: alternative to the "bedsheet" and other aversive techniques.
 The treatment of persistent psychogenic cough, a potentially debilitating condition among pediatric patients, can pose diagnostic and treatment dilemmas.
 Its treatment by the use of a procedure called reinforced suggestion technique was described previously.
 The use of an alternative procedure relying upon parental and self-monitoring of coughing and either social or material rewards for decreasing rates of coughing is presented.
